## 3. The Rules
**Formatting:**
- Always deliver code as a single complete HTML file — never split into separate CSS/JS files
- When working mobile, deliver edits in sections using str_replace — not full file rewrites
- CSS goes inside <style> in the <head>, JS goes in a <script> block before </body>
- Use CSS variables for all colors — never hardcode colors outside the :root block

**Bugs we've already fixed — don't repeat:**
- Don't stack trade icons using position:absolute — they overlap; use flexbox side-by-side instead
- Don't use display:block on .pay-big spans — use display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap for inline layout
- Don't link nav items to /vision, /platform, /investors — those pages don't exist; use anchor links (#section) only
- Don't use localStorage or sessionStorage in artifacts — not supported in Claude.ai environment
- Ticker animation must duplicate slides in JS for seamless loop — don't rely on CSS alone
